b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe01142.htm)  [Next](sbe01144.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBW6/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 1 (SBE01)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### NINTH KHA _N_ _D_ A.\n\n1\\. 'Food (anna) is better than power. Therefore if a man abstain from food\nfor ten days, though he live, he would be unable to see, hear, perceive,\nthink, act, and understand. But when he obtains\n\np. 117\n\nfood, he is able to see, hear, perceive, think, act, and understand. Meditate\non food.\n\n2\\. 'He who meditates on food as Brahman, obtains the worlds rich in food and\ndrink; he is, as it were, lord and master as far as food reaches--he who\nmeditates on food as Brahman.'\n\n'Sir, is there something better than food\n\n'Yes, there is something better than food.'\n\n'Sir, tell it me.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: VII, 10](sbe01144.htm)\n\n"